Package com.milk.objed

Interface Summary
Editable This interface is for objects which want to declare that they have a publicly editable aspect.
Editor This interface is mostly just to mark objects which know how to perform edits on another object but does have a couple of actual method definitions.
FieldsEditor This interface is for Editors that manage an object with field-like sub-parts.
ValueEditor This interface is for editors which are effictively just editing a single value, such as a string or boolean value.
 

Class Summary
AutoUpdater An AutoUpdater is used to cause a set of editors to be told to update themselves at a regular basis.
BaseEditor This is a base class that handles a lot of stuff for editors.
BaseFieldsEditor This class merely serves as an abstract class extending BaseEditor and implementing (fully abstractly) FieldsEditor.
BaseWrappedValueEditor This is a base class which implements ValueEditor to defer to some other target editor.
CheckboxEditor This class is an editor which wraps around a ValueEditor, only allowing for getting and setting as a Boolean, intended to be presented as a checkbox.
DirectValueEditor This class is a ValueEditor whose managed value is directly held in the object.
FieldValueEditor This is a ValueEditor which uses reflection to access a particular public field of a target object.
FixedFieldsEditor This is an implementation of FieldsEditor which keeps a fixed list of fields.
IntegerTextEditor This is an editor for integer values as text.
MethodValueEditor This is a ValueEditor which uses reflection to access a getter and setter method which collectively act like a field on a given target.
PublicFields This class merely holds a static helper method to make creating Editors for public objects easier.
StringTextEditor This is an editor for string values as text.
TextEditor This class is an editor which wraps around a ValueEditor, only allowing for getting and setting as a text string.
 

Exception Summary
UneditableException This exception is thrown when something wants to edit an object that isn't editable.
